        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 3:47PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Iraan Municipal Airport, or 17 miles north of Sheffield, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Crockett County.

This includes Interstate 10 near Mile Marker 327.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
